{
  "stem": "26276.3",
  "chunk_idx": 4,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 10.4,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And I says to him, you knew what had went on in there.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "He started shaking, denying again, until I pointed the rifle at him.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Then he says, yes, he knew about it.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "He was in the army himself but he couldn't do or think about it, and that was the answer of most of them.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "Most of them, they just like to see the killings of Jews.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "You know, and I was so full of hate that I pulled the bullet-- that I pulled that-- the, the thing, and I killed him.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And nobody of the Eighth Army would say a thing.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "They didn't care.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "They gave us almost a week long to go out and do whatever we want.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And if we asked any soldier of giving us gun or rifle, they would take off the rifle from their own shoulder and give it to us.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "Because when they came into camp and they saw with their own eyes what they did see, they sat down and they were crying like kids.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "That's how terrible it was that they couldn't take it.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Yes.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "I was.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "The main thing that I did go out was, at that day, to go out to look for food.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "That was the main thing.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "But when we-- when I saw a man in there, I knew that man had to be-- or had to know.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "Either he was in the army or he is in the army or he knew everything that had went on in there, especially when you live so close by to the camp.",
      "word_count": 32
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "Couldn't have missed it.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "At the same time, it happened even when the Americans-- the day that we woke up, the last day of the liberation, we went out-- they call it appellplatz, where we gather.",
      "word_count": 32
    }
  ],
